1
00:00:33,541 --> 00:00:37,041
IT WAS RAINING
THAT DAY, AS WELL.

2
00:00:37,791 --> 00:00:41,750
AND SO YOU DIDN'T COME
BECAUSE OF THE RAIN?

3
00:00:42,125 --> 00:00:46,375
I WAS SUPPOSED TO KILL YOU.
IT WAS ALL SET UP.

4
00:00:48,291 --> 00:00:50,250
IF I HAD...

5
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:53,333
I WOULD'VE BEEN FREE.

6
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:01,541
SO WHY DIDN'T YOU?

7
00:01:02,166 --> 00:01:06,041
YOU CHOSE TO BE HUNTED. WHY?

8
00:01:06,125 --> 00:01:08,666
WHY DID YOU LOVE ME?

9
00:01:18,291 --> 00:01:21,500
LET'S JUST GO AWAY SOMEWHERE.

10
00:01:21,583 --> 00:01:24,583
ESCAPE. VANISH.

11
00:01:24,666 --> 00:01:27,875
GO SOMEWHERE WHERE
THERE'S NO ONE ELSE.

12
00:01:30,791 --> 00:01:33,541
JUST THE TWO OF US.

13
00:01:45,375 --> 00:01:48,083
[FOOTSTEPS]

14
00:01:54,625 --> 00:01:57,416
WAS THE TARGET TERMINATED?

15
00:01:58,708 --> 00:02:00,666
HE GOT AWAY.

16
00:02:02,666 --> 00:02:04,083
OUR AGENTS WERE CUT DOWN.

17
00:02:04,166 --> 00:02:07,208
THEY RAN OUT OF FIREPOWER
AND WERE UNABLE TO TAKE OUT--

18
00:02:07,291 --> 00:02:09,583
WHY DID YOU COME BACK?

19
00:02:09,666 --> 00:02:12,500
WHERE'S JULIA?

20
00:02:13,375 --> 00:02:16,000
I COULDN'T FIND HER.

21
00:02:16,083 --> 00:02:17,458
[FOOTSTEPS]

22
00:02:17,541 --> 00:02:20,250
[INAUDIBLE]

23
00:02:23,583 --> 00:02:29,375
CHINN, DO NOT FOLLOW
IN YOUR BROTHER'S FOOTSTEPS.

24
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:40,916
KEEP GOING.
JUST DRIVE PAST IT.

25
00:02:46,916 --> 00:02:48,000
WHAT?

26
00:02:48,083 --> 00:02:50,833
SOMEBODY MIGHT'VE
GOTTEN THERE ALREADY.

27
00:02:51,458 --> 00:02:53,375
WAIT HERE.

28
00:02:59,916 --> 00:03:01,083
ANNIE?

29
00:03:01,166 --> 00:03:03,750
[MOANING SOFTLY]

30
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:09,833
I TOLD THEM YOU WEREN'T HERE.

31
00:03:09,916 --> 00:03:12,250
I SAID YOU WERE ALREADY DEAD.

32
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:15,041
TOLD THEM THEY WERE
WASTING THEIR TIME.

33
00:03:15,125 --> 00:03:16,375
DON'T TALK.

34
00:03:16,458 --> 00:03:20,416
VICIOUS ASSASSINATED
ALL OF THE ELDERS.

35
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:23,333
THAT'S WHAT THEY SAID.

36
00:03:24,583 --> 00:03:29,041
EVERYONE. THEY'VE ALL LOST THEIR
SENSE OF PLACE IN THE WORLD,

37
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:32,541
LIKE KITES WITHOUT
STRINGS OR TAILS.

38
00:03:32,625 --> 00:03:34,500
[GASPS]

39
00:03:34,583 --> 00:03:38,833
OH, SO YOU FOUND JULIA.
THAT'S GOOD.

40
00:03:38,916 --> 00:03:41,416
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU.

41
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,500
ANNIE.

42
00:03:43,583 --> 00:03:47,375
IT GOT A LITTLE CHILLY TODAY.

43
00:03:47,458 --> 00:03:50,625
IT'S THOSE COLD WINDS.

44
00:04:07,625 --> 00:04:10,166
[FOOTSTEPS]

45
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:19,750
YOU WON'T NEED
ALL THOSE WEAPONS

46
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:23,541
IF WE RUN AWAY TOGETHER.
YOU KNOW THAT.

47
00:04:25,583 --> 00:04:28,000
YOU'RE STAYING.

48
00:04:32,375 --> 00:04:34,916
THEN I'LL STAY, TOO.

49
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:38,708
I'LL BE WITH YOU UNTIL THE END.

50
00:04:42,583 --> 00:04:44,750
[COCKS RIFLE]

51
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:48,041
I'M SORRY. I'M GONNA MAKE
A BIT OF A SCENE.

52
00:04:52,958 --> 00:04:56,000
[METAL CLANKING]

53
00:05:05,208 --> 00:05:07,291
YOU'RE A VERY LUCKY WOMAN.

54
00:05:07,375 --> 00:05:08,500
YEAH, RIGHT.

55
00:05:08,583 --> 00:05:10,791
MY TIMING WAS PERFECT
FOR GETTING SHOT AT

56
00:05:10,875 --> 00:05:12,125
AND NEARLY KILLED.

57
00:05:12,208 --> 00:05:13,625
I'M REALLY ON A ROLL.

58
00:05:13,708 --> 00:05:16,500
THE RED TAIL WON'T BE
FUNCTIONAL FOR AWHILE.

59
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:19,083
YOU'RE HAVING SOME
PRETTY GOOD LUCK YOURSELF.

60
00:05:19,166 --> 00:05:22,750
THAT SPIKE; HE WAS
NOTHING BUT TROUBLE.

61
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:25,083
HE'S PROBABLY NOT COMING BACK.

62
00:05:25,166 --> 00:05:28,000
THEY MAY HAVE KILLED HIM
ALREADY, YOU KNOW.

63
00:05:28,083 --> 00:05:29,250
IT'S POSSIBLE.

64
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:31,750
SO WHAT? YOU WANT ME
TO GO LOOKING FOR HIM?

65
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:34,958
FORGET IT. HE'S DEALING
WITH HIS OWN PAST.

66
00:05:35,041 --> 00:05:37,375
IT'S HIS FIGHT.

67
00:05:37,833 --> 00:05:40,666
YOU TOLD HIM TO GO AFTER HER.

68
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:43,291
MY LEG IS WRECKED,
MY SHIP IS BUSTED.

69
00:05:43,375 --> 00:05:45,458
HELL, YES. HE WAS
NOTHING BUT TROUBLE,

70
00:05:45,541 --> 00:05:48,208
AND I DON'T GIVE A DAMN.

71
00:05:54,375 --> 00:05:56,750
SO, WHAT KIND OF WOMAN IS SHE?

72
00:05:56,833 --> 00:05:59,083
WHAT'S JULIA LIKE?

73
00:05:59,166 --> 00:06:00,833
ORDINARY.

74
00:06:00,916 --> 00:06:03,291
THE KIND OF DANGEROUS,
BEAUTIFUL ORDINARY

75
00:06:03,375 --> 00:06:06,291
THAT YOU JUST CAN'T LEAVE ALONE.

76
00:06:06,375 --> 00:06:07,958
I SEE.

77
00:06:08,041 --> 00:06:10,458
LIKE AN ANGEL
FROM THE UNDERWORLD.

78
00:06:10,541 --> 00:06:14,625
OR MAYBE A DEVIL FROM PARADISE.

79
00:06:17,666 --> 00:06:20,416
[GUNFIRE]

80
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:27,416
UGH!

81
00:06:32,208 --> 00:06:34,000
AAH!

82
00:06:43,458 --> 00:06:45,500
THIS WAY.

83
00:06:47,125 --> 00:06:49,291
GET DOWN!

84
00:06:53,916 --> 00:06:55,750
[CLICKS]

85
00:06:58,041 --> 00:06:59,708
UGH!

86
00:07:14,125 --> 00:07:16,250
[GASPING]

87
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,041
JULIA!

88
00:07:42,375 --> 00:07:44,000
JULIA.

89
00:07:44,083 --> 00:07:46,416
[SOFT MOAN]

90
00:07:51,208 --> 00:07:53,875
[INAUDIBLE]

91
00:08:23,125 --> 00:08:24,458
WHERE'S SPIKE?

92
00:08:24,541 --> 00:08:28,541
CAN YOU HELP ME TRACK HIM DOWN?

93
00:08:28,625 --> 00:08:32,625
ALL LIVING THINGS, EVERY
BEING THAT WALKS AND BREATHES,

94
00:08:32,708 --> 00:08:34,916
EACH HAS ITS OWN STAR.

95
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,083
HUH?

96
00:08:36,166 --> 00:08:39,458
WHEN A LIFE IS BORN,
A NEW STAR APPEARS.

97
00:08:39,541 --> 00:08:41,250
THAT IS THE GUARDIAN STAR.

98
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:43,208
THE STAR THAT WARMS THIS PLANET

99
00:08:43,291 --> 00:08:46,541
IS SOMEONE'S
GUARDIAN STAR, AS WELL.

100
00:08:46,625 --> 00:08:51,916
THE RED STAR YOU SEE OVERHEAD;
THE BLUE STAR ON THE HORIZON.

101
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:58,375
AND WHEN A LIFE ENDS,
THE STAR FALLS AND DISAPPEARS.

102
00:08:58,458 --> 00:08:59,750
DON'T SAY THAT.

103
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:00,916
YOU, RUNNING ROCK...

104
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,250
THAT'S NOT MY NAME.
DON'T CALL ME THAT.

105
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:08,875
HIS STAR IS ABOUT TO FALL.
I HAVE DREAMED IT.

106
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:12,875
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.
WHAT AM I DOING HERE?

107
00:09:12,958 --> 00:09:17,791
DO NOT FEAR DEATH.
DEATH IS ALWAYS AT OUR SIDE.

108
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:21,791
WHEN WE SHOW FEAR, IT JUMPS
AT US FASTER THAN LIGHT,

109
00:09:21,875 --> 00:09:28,125
BUT IF WE DO NOT SHOW FEAR,
IT CASTS ITS EYE UPON US GENTLY

110
00:09:28,208 --> 00:09:30,375
AND THEN GUIDES US
INTO INFINITY.

111
00:09:37,583 --> 00:09:39,291
VICIOUS, HERE IT IS.

112
00:09:39,375 --> 00:09:41,833
HER PASSPORT WAS STILL
INSIDE THE POCKET.

113
00:09:41,916 --> 00:09:45,958
IT'LL BE IMPOSSIBLE FOR THEM
TO ESCAPE THE PLANET NOW.

114
00:09:46,041 --> 00:09:49,541
A BEAST THAT HAS
LOST HIS PLACE.

115
00:09:49,625 --> 00:09:53,583
HE HAS NOWHERE TO RETURN TO NOW.

116
00:09:53,666 --> 00:09:56,375
HE WILL COME.

117
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:13,166
[GASPS]

118
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:16,041
SPIKE, YOU'RE... YOU'RE BACK.

119
00:10:16,125 --> 00:10:18,625
YOU HAVE ANYTHING TO EAT?

120
00:10:18,708 --> 00:10:19,291
HUH?

121
00:10:19,375 --> 00:10:22,041
I'M REALLY STARVING.

122
00:10:30,291 --> 00:10:33,833
THIS FOOD TASTES
TERRIBLE, AS USUAL.

123
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:37,458
FOR BEING SO BAD,
YOU SURE EAT A LOT OF IT.

124
00:10:37,541 --> 00:10:40,916
THEY SAY HUNGER
IS THE BEST SPICE.

125
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,458
HA HA HA.

126
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:46,875
EVER HEARD THIS STORY?

127
00:10:46,958 --> 00:10:48,083
HUH?

128
00:10:48,166 --> 00:10:50,541
THERE ONCE WAS
A TIGER-STRIPED CAT.

129
00:10:50,625 --> 00:10:53,458
THIS CAT DIED A MILLION DEATHS,

130
00:10:53,541 --> 00:10:55,875
REVIVED, AND LIVED
A MILLION LIVES,

131
00:10:55,958 --> 00:10:58,375
AND HE WAS OWNED
BY VARIOUS PEOPLE

132
00:10:58,458 --> 00:11:00,416
WHO HE DIDN'T REALLY CARE FOR.

133
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:04,083
THE CAT WASN'T AFRAID TO DIE.

134
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:09,125
THEN ONE DAY, THE CAT
BECAME A STRAY CAT,

135
00:11:09,208 --> 00:11:11,125
WHICH MEANT HE WAS FREE.

136
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:13,000
HE MET A WHITE FEMALE CAT,

137
00:11:13,083 --> 00:11:16,500
AND THE TWO OF THEM SPENT
THEIR DAYS TOGETHER HAPPILY.

138
00:11:16,583 --> 00:11:18,041
WELL, YEARS PASSED

139
00:11:18,125 --> 00:11:21,166
AND THE WHITE CAT GREW WEAK
AND DIED OF OLD AGE.

140
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:25,291
THE TIGER-STRIPED CAT
CRIED A MILLION TIMES,

141
00:11:25,375 --> 00:11:26,958
THEN HE DIED, TOO,

142
00:11:27,041 --> 00:11:31,916
EXCEPT THIS TIME,
HE DIDN'T COME BACK TO LIFE.

143
00:11:34,041 --> 00:11:36,250
YEAH. IT'S A GOOD STORY.

144
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:37,625
I HATE THAT STORY.

145
00:11:37,708 --> 00:11:38,916
HUH?

146
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:42,541
I NEVER LIKED CATS.
YOU KNOW THAT.

147
00:11:42,625 --> 00:11:44,750
OH, YEAH. THAT'S RIGHT.

148
00:11:44,833 --> 00:11:47,250
HEH.

149
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:50,416
[BOTH LAUGHING]

150
00:11:57,041 --> 00:11:58,333
HEY, SPIKE.

151
00:11:58,416 --> 00:12:00,083
YEAH?

152
00:12:00,166 --> 00:12:02,125
I JUST WANT TO
ASK YOU ONE THING.

153
00:12:02,208 --> 00:12:03,458
WHAT'S THAT?

154
00:12:03,541 --> 00:12:06,125
IS IT FOR THE GIRL?

155
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:09,041
SHE'S DEAD.

156
00:12:09,125 --> 00:12:12,416
THERE'S NOTHING
I CAN DO FOR HER NOW.

157
00:12:21,666 --> 00:12:22,333
[CLICK]

158
00:12:22,416 --> 00:12:25,208
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

159
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:29,125
WHY ARE YOU GOING?

160
00:12:31,708 --> 00:12:34,791
YOU TOLD ME ONCE
TO FORGET THE PAST

161
00:12:34,875 --> 00:12:37,708
'CAUSE IT DOESN'T MATTER...

162
00:12:38,166 --> 00:12:42,333
BUT YOU'RE THE ONE STILL
TIED TO THE PAST, SPIKE!

163
00:12:44,958 --> 00:12:47,416
LOOK AT MY EYES, FAYE.

164
00:12:48,125 --> 00:12:52,875
ONE OF THEM IS A FAKE 'CAUSE
I LOST IT IN AN ACCIDENT.

165
00:12:52,958 --> 00:12:57,833
SINCE THEN, I'VE BEEN
SEEING THE PAST IN ONE EYE

166
00:12:57,916 --> 00:12:59,625
AND THE PRESENT IN THE OTHER,

167
00:12:59,708 --> 00:13:03,333
SO I THOUGHT I COULD ONLY SEE
PATCHES OF REALITY,

168
00:13:03,416 --> 00:13:05,916
NEVER THE WHOLE PICTURE.

169
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,416
DON'T TELL ME
THINGS LIKE THAT.

170
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:11,958
YOU'VE NEVER TOLD ME
ANYTHING ABOUT YOURSELF,

171
00:13:12,041 --> 00:13:13,458
SO DON'T TELL ME NOW.

172
00:13:13,541 --> 00:13:18,291
I FELT LIKE I WAS WATCHING
A DREAM I'D NEVER WAKE UP FROM.

173
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:24,208
HMM. BEFORE I KNEW IT,
THE DREAM WAS ALL OVER.

174
00:13:26,166 --> 00:13:30,333
MY MEMORY FINALLY CAME BACK,

175
00:13:30,416 --> 00:13:34,916
BUT NOTHING GOOD CAME OF IT.

176
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:37,500
THERE WAS NO PLACE
FOR ME TO RETURN TO.

177
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:40,666
THIS WAS THE ONLY PLACE
I COULD GO.

178
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:44,416
AND NOW YOU'RE LEAVING,
JUST LIKE THAT!

179
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:47,625
WHY DO YOU HAVE TO GO?

180
00:13:47,708 --> 00:13:49,666
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

181
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:51,583
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO?

182
00:13:51,666 --> 00:13:55,208
JUST THROW YOU LIFE AWAY
LIKE IT WAS NOTHING?

183
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:59,166
I'M NOT GOING THERE TO DIE.

184
00:13:59,250 --> 00:14:03,875
I'M GOING TO FIND OUT
IF I'M REALLY ALIVE.

185
00:14:03,958 --> 00:14:06,416
I HAVE TO DO IT, FAYE.

186
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:13,708
[FIRES GUN]

187
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:49,375
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

188
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,416
[GUNFIRE]

189
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:12,750
UGH!

190
00:16:14,291 --> 00:16:16,125
UGH.

191
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:18,000
CHINN.

192
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:20,583
WHERE'S VICIOUS?

193
00:16:20,666 --> 00:16:23,583
ON THE TOP FLOOR.
THIS WAY.

194
00:16:38,666 --> 00:16:40,666
CHINN!

195
00:16:42,583 --> 00:16:46,125
[MOANING]

196
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:47,708
CHINN!

197
00:16:47,791 --> 00:16:51,166
VICIOUS... HAS GOT
TO BE STOPPED.

198
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:57,083
I... WAS WAITING FOR YOU
TO COME BACK AND TAKE OVER.

199
00:16:57,166 --> 00:16:59,708
UGH.

200
00:17:27,416 --> 00:17:30,250
SO, YOU'RE FINALLY AWAKE.

201
00:17:30,333 --> 00:17:32,250
I TOLD YOU BEFORE, SPIKE,

202
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:35,666
I'M THE ONLY ONE WHO CAN
KILL YOU AND SET YOU FREE.

203
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:38,958
THOSE WORDS APPLY
TO YOU, AS WELL, VICIOUS.

204
00:17:39,041 --> 00:17:43,416
EITHER WAY,
IT'S GOING TO END HERE.

205
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:56,500
[GRUNTING]

206
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:15,041
JULIA IS DEAD.

207
00:18:16,458 --> 00:18:18,500
LET'S FINISH IT NOW.

208
00:18:18,583 --> 00:18:21,500
AS YOU WISH.

209
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:52,375
IT'S ALL A... DREAM.

210
00:18:52,458 --> 00:18:57,083
YEAH. JUST A DREAM.

211
00:19:23,541 --> 00:19:25,958
BANG.

212
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:24,166
♪ NEVER SEEN A BLUER SKY ♪

213
00:20:24,666 --> 00:20:30,791
♪ YEAH, I CAN FEEL IT
REACHING OUT AND MOVING CLOSER ♪

214
00:20:32,541 --> 00:20:36,333
♪ THERE'S SOMETHING ABOUT BLUE ♪

215
00:20:45,208 --> 00:20:49,541
♪ ASKED MYSELF
WHAT IT'S ALL FOR ♪

216
00:20:49,625 --> 00:20:55,583
♪ YOU KNOW THE FUNNY THING
ABOUT IT, I COULDN'T ANSWER ♪

217
00:20:57,708 --> 00:21:01,041
♪ NO, I COULDN'T ANSWER ♪

218
00:21:04,791 --> 00:21:09,541
♪ THINGS HAVE TURNED
A DEEPER SHADE OF BLUE ♪

219
00:21:09,625 --> 00:21:16,166
♪ AND IMAGES THAT MIGHT BE REAL
MAY BE ILLUSION ♪

220
00:21:17,708 --> 00:21:22,166
♪ KEEP FLASHING OFF AND ON ♪

221
00:21:23,833 --> 00:21:31,708
♪ FREE... ♪

222
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:40,666
♪ WANNA BE FREE ♪

223
00:21:42,833 --> 00:21:51,666
♪ GONNA BE FREE ♪

224
00:21:53,166 --> 00:21:57,458
♪ AND MOVE AMONG THE STARS ♪

225
00:21:57,541 --> 00:22:02,333
♪ YOU KNOW THEY
REALLY AREN'T SO FAR ♪

226
00:22:02,416 --> 00:22:10,125
♪ FEELS SO FREE... ♪

227
00:22:12,708 --> 00:22:22,666
♪ GOT TO KNOW FREE... ♪

228
00:22:23,333 --> 00:22:31,750
♪ PLEASE... ♪

229
00:22:32,583 --> 00:22:36,625
♪ DON'T WAKE ME FROM THE DREAM ♪

230
00:22:37,458 --> 00:22:42,666
♪ IT'S REALLY
EVERYTHING IT SEEMED ♪

231
00:22:42,750 --> 00:22:47,250
♪ I'M SO FREE... ♪

232
00:22:47,791 --> 00:22:56,625
♪ NO BLACK AND WHITE
IN THE BLUE ♪

233
00:22:56,708 --> 00:23:00,708
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

234
00:23:59,500 --> 00:24:02,875
♪ EVERYTHING IS CLEARER NOW ♪

235
00:24:04,250 --> 00:24:07,000
♪ LIFE IS JUST A DREAM,
YOU KNOW ♪

236
00:24:07,083 --> 00:24:10,250
♪ THAT'S NEVER ENDING ♪

237
00:24:12,916 --> 00:24:14,916
♪ I'M ASCENDING ♪

